The paper discusses the development of a multi-agent reinforcement learning algorithm for a hidden role game, which involves cooperation and uncertainty among teammates. This suggests a focus on AI and game theory, which are covered by the cs.AI and cs.GT sub-categories. The use of deep value networks and self-play also suggests a focus on machine learning, which is covered by the cs.LG sub-category. The paper specifically addresses the challenge of cooperation, which suggests a focus on multi-agent systems, covered by the cs.MA sub-category. Finally, the use of empirical game-theoretic methods suggests a focus on social and information networks, covered by the cs.SI sub-category.
